window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>Does real love, great love, still exist? Or have online texting, sexting and ghosting ruined romance forever?</p> <p>Cupid, about to be kicked upstairs for lack of work, has one last chance to prove that love is alive and well. His targets? Two strangers who have sworn off romance.</p> <p>Eve, a once-famous ballerina now happily running her family farm in Vermont, was too busy dancing to be swept away by passion. Evan, a sought-after San Francisco anthologist, prefers all his passions without strings. When they meet, the sparks are otherworldly….but when their real worlds collide, Cupid admits he’s way out of his depth.</p> <p>In a luminous narration by celebrated voice actor Jill Smith, How to Fall in Love: A Novel weaves earthly wisdom, celestial mischief, and a touch of famous literature into a magical story about second chances.</p>"; 
